FT  28 NOV 92 / UK Company News: Brockhampton surges 55%
Mainly as result of keeping operating costs in check Brockhampton Holdings,
parent of Portsmouth Water, saw its pre-tax profit surge 55 per cent to
Pounds 1.87m in the six months ended September 30 1992.
Furthermore, the directors forecast maintenance of the current levels of
performance in the second half.
Turnover rose 8 per cent to Pounds 11.7m despite a further decline
industrial consumption.
Earnings per share doubled to 15.6p (7.9p). The interim dividend is raised
to 2.2p (1.65p).
